OL,3,CLebanon's deputy PM tells ITV News he
OL,4,Cfears country faces prolonged war
OL,6,FThese are difficult, dangerous days in
OL,7,FLebanon, and this country, which is no
OL,8,Fstranger to the challenges of war,
OL,9,Ffinds itself unsure of what is to come.
OL,11,FAsk anyone here, "What is your
OL,12,Ffeeling?" And you get the same answer.
OL,14,FAs one senior politician put it,
OL,15,F"Every day I wake up with a different
OL,16,Fgut feeling, but every day I know it's
OL,17,Fnot going to be good."
OL,19,FThe civilian death toll is rising, and
OL,20,Fnowhere feels safe.
OL,26,@tD@IO]wD@AOUyD@VO]
